description._content: This posed shot is significant in that one of the principle funders of the Center, businessman and philanthropist George Kaplan is in the photo. The Jewish Educational Center was the precursor to the St. Paul JCC. It served as a recreation and education, and by 1939 over 100 community groups, including Boy and Girl Scouts, a theater company, and two orchestra were using the facility. Date: 1940? Source: JCC Photo Collection; 23.5 cm x 18.3 cm Format: Black and white original photo Subject: Sports and recreation; St Paul Jewish Community Center Coverage: St. Paul; Ramsey; Minnesota; United States Local Identifier: X.21 Link to our record: http://reflections.mndigital.org/u?/jhs,24 From the Steinfeldt Photography Collection of the Jewish Historical Society of the Upper Midwest.
